Company: Universities Admissions Centre (NSW & ACT) Pty Ltd
Ad Text:
Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) – NSW & ACT

The Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) is the largest tertiary admissions centre in Australia. We believe in the value of education and are committed to providing opportunities in higher education for all members of our community.




What we do

The Universities Admissions Centre (UAC) was established in 1995 and is the largest tertiary admissions centre in Australia. Owned by universities in NSW and the ACT, UAC’s mission is to provide excellence in admissions services, including the calculation of the Australian Tertiary Admission Rank (ATAR).

Our Corporate Finance department is an integral part of UAC’s operations providing specialised support to UAC’s Board, Executive and staff, ensuring that UAC’s financial resourcing and objectives align with the organisation's strategic objectives and contribute to its overall success.

We’re now looking for a Financial Planning and Analysis (FP&A) Manager to contribute to UAC’s success.

 

About the Role

UAC is seeking an experienced FP&A Manager to join the Corporate Finance department.

As a FP&A Manager, you are responsible for leading financial planning, forecasting, performance analysis, and strategic financial support across the Admissions Centre. The role supports organisational sustainability by providing high-quality financial insights that inform service delivery, student application processing, technology investment, and stakeholder partnership decisions.

Working closely with executive leadership, institutional partners, and operational teams, the role ensures financial planning aligns with sector trends, regulatory requirements, and organisational strategy.




About You

To succeed in this role, you will have:

Completion of a tertiary qualification in Finance, Accounting, Commerce, or a related discipline; and CPA, CA, or equivalent professional qualification; or an equivalent combination of extensive experience and/or education/training.
Demonstrated experience in financial planning, budgeting, and forecasting, with strong financial modelling, analytical and problem-solving capability.
Experience supporting senior stakeholders with the ability to translate financial data into clear operational insights.
Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills, with the ability to work collaboratively across technical and operational teams.
Demonstrated attention to detail with a strong focus on governance, compliance, and financial integrity.
Proven commercial acumen and strategic thinking, with the ability to link financial insights to organisational objectives.

Why Join UAC?
We’re a dynamic organisation and proud to offer excellent conditions, including a competitive remuneration package, generous staff benefits, and a genuine work/life balance.

We provide flexibility for our staff who are continuing to work from home and the office.

We have the technology platforms and ethos to ensure our remote teams continue to stay connected!

This is an excellent opportunity to be part of the continued success of UAC as we deliver cutting-edge platforms that facilitate lifelong learning.

Competitive salary and generous staff benefits.
Flexible work arrangements and a strong commitment to work-life balance.
Opportunities to lead high-impact projects that shape the education sector.
A collaborative, inclusive workplace that values innovation and professional growth.

Remuneration: The annual salary range is $164,630.84 – $173,704.09 pa (includes base salary plus 17% employer superannuation contribution and annual leave loading).

Ready to Make an Impact?

If this is an opportunity of interest to you, please download the Information Package  from our website at: uac.edu.au/jobs. Apply now!

For your application to be considered, you must provide a written response to each of the selection criteria described in the Position Description.

Questions?

For any questions, email jobs@uac.edu.au

By submitting your application, you confirm you consent to the UAC Privacy Policy for Job Applicants

About the role

We’re all about helping our members make the most of their money. And while they go after their goals, you can too. We’re looking for a manager to support building and embedding a contemporary Line 1 risk governance, reporting and insights function within our Business Risk Management team. You’ll support the establishment of the strategy, be part of a high‑performing team, and partner with senior leaders across the enterprise to uplift risk maturity and drive consistent practices aligned to ART’s Risk Management Framework.

 

Day to day, you'll:

Support the Risk Governance team’s strategy and operating model;
Ensure effective risk forums and rhythms are in place across the enterprise; coordinate Line 1 risk reporting for executive and board forums; identify enterprise‑wide insights and priorities.
Lead the annual Trustee Risk Management Declaration and support risk appetite metric assessment and reporting.
Participate to the maintenance of a Line 1 risk community of practice across the enterprise and lift risk capability across the business.
Design and implement Line 1 risk reporting and analytics frameworks; leverage AI and emerging tech to deliver efficient, decision‑ready insights.
Partner with the business, their line 1 risk managers, Line 2 and Line 3 to embed robust risk culture and practices and contribute to board‑level reporting.

This role is a permanent opportunity. 

About you

It goes without saying you'll be a great communicator with top notch interpersonal skills. We'll also expect you to pick up problems and come up with quick, creative ways to solve them. It's quite likely you tick some of the following boxes too:  

Tertiary qualifications in Risk, Business, Law or related discipline.
Deep knowledge of enterprise/operational risk and compliance within superannuation/insurance‑in‑super, including APRA prudential standards.
Strong Line 1 and/or Line 2 experience across governance, control frameworks, incident management, analytics and Board reporting.
Strong experience within the Financial Services industry, especially within Superannuation industry
Proven team leadership and change capability; able to operate at pace amid ambiguity while balancing BAU, future design and transformation.

Our 2.4 million members trust us to take care of over $330 billion in retirement savings. And we help them take charge of their finances and face the future with confidence. About the Role

The Senior Business Analyst leads complex, enterprise-wide analysis within the EDO, designing scalable solutions that align with UNSW’s strategic goals. By defining business needs, process improvements, and data requirements, the role ensures all outcomes are practical and institutional priorities are met.

As a key influencer in business and technology decisions, the role mentors other analysts and advances university-wide analysis standards and tools. Reporting to the Director – Data Transformation, this position carries no direct reports.

The successful applicant will possess and have experience in:

Lead end-to-end business analysis for enterprise-level initiatives, covering everything from initial business case development to post-implementation reviews.
Partner with senior stakeholders to align business and technology outcomes with UNSW’s strategic objectives and assess organizational impacts.
Design and document complex "as-is" and "to-be" processes and solution models across multiple data domains and functional units.
Define and recommend specialized business analysis approaches, toolsets, and standards for major University projects and programs.
Mentor and guide other business analysts to ensure workstream consistency and alignment with enterprise architecture and project goals.
Collaborate with technical teams, including architects and developers, to ensure solutions satisfy both business needs and technical constraints.
Drive enterprise testing activities by defining test cases and leading user acceptance testing (UAT) to validate business requirements.

About You

Hold a relevant tertiary qualification combined with extensive experience leading strategic, enterprise-scale initiatives in large, complex organizations.
Demonstrate proficiency in operating effectively across diverse delivery frameworks, including Agile, Waterfall, and Hybrid environments.
Possess high-level expertise in core analysis tools for process mapping, requirements elicitation, data analysis, and solution evaluation.
Exhibit a proven track record in developing business cases, managing vendor selection, and supporting the implementation of enterprise platforms.
Apply advanced analytical and problem-solving skills to assess complex system interdependencies and deliver practical, scalable solutions.
Exercise outstanding communication and negotiation skills to bridge gaps between executive sponsors, technical teams, and diverse end users.
Provide leadership through mentoring, guiding, and reviewing the work of other analysts to ensure high-quality, consistent deliverables.

For further information on the role & responsibilities, please refer to the Position Description

Company Description

About SEEK

At SEEK, we serve a noble purpose: to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and to help organisations succeed.

By joining us, you’ll be part of a multi-national technology business that is far-reaching with a start-up working culture that focuses on a set of collaborative values and appreciates dynamic cultures. SEEK is a place where potential meets possibility – it’s where your career aspiration and our purpose can make great things happen.

Why join us?

Be part of a multi-national tech company with strong core values to help us solve complex challenges for our customers while building a flexible, exciting career – one that could take you anywhere.

We’re looking for people who thrive in dynamic teams and enjoy tackling regular new challenges in a large-scale, modern, and agile environment. As one of Asia Pacific’s largest tech companies, you’ll contribute to multi-lingual systems, solving high-impact problems to the benefit of millions of people within the region.

Be part of a fast-growing company with a strong culture and clear purpose, innovation and strong investment in responsible AI. SEEK offers you the opportunity to be involved in impactful work and be part of a great team. Expect a great investment in your career development with access to workshops, conferences and courses while you work alongside seasoned experts.

Job Description

The Role

Join SEEK’s Investor Relations team in a high-impact senior role. You will be instrumental in executing our IR program, with a primary focus on delivering seamless half-year and full-year financial reporting.

This position offers significant exposure to senior leadership and external stakeholders. We are looking for a strategic thinker with exceptional communication skills and sound judgment who balances high-level quality with a "roll-up-your-sleeves" attitude. You will report directly to the Head of Investor Relations.

Key Responsibilities

Strategic Investor Relations & Market Positioning

Program Development: Support the evolution of SEEK’s investor relations strategy to maintain world-class external relationships.

Valuation Support: Co-lead initiatives that sharpen SEEK’s market positioning and build long-term shareholder confidence.

Strategic Feedback: Act as a vital link between the market and the Board, translating external sentiment into internal strategic advice.

External Reporting & Disclosure

Results Leadership: Co-lead the end-to-end delivery of Half-Year and Full-Year results, including ASX announcements and AGM materials.

Narrative Crafting: Develop clear, compelling stories that explain SEEK’s financial performance, product strategy, and future outlook.

Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner with Finance, Strategy, and Product teams to gather the data and insights needed for high-quality disclosures.

Investor & Analyst Engagement

Market Interface: Manage day-to-day interactions with sell-side analysts and respond to detailed inquiries.

Investor Relations: Join the Head of IR in high-level meetings and roadshows with buy-side institutional investors.

Targeting & Registry: Monitor the shareholder register and support initiatives to attract new, long-term investors.

Market Intelligence & Internal Insights

Analyst Monitoring: Analyze research reports to extract key market themes and competitor benchmarks.

Performance Tracking: Keep a pulse on broker consensus, investor sentiment, and share price movements.

Board Reporting: Synthesize complex market data into concise, actionable briefings for SEEK’s leadership and Board of Directors

Qualifications
Minimum 7 years of relevant experience in investor relations, equity research, investment banking, corporate finance, or financial communications
Strong commercial and financial acumen with the ability to analyse and interpret financial statements
Exceptional stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence and engage confidently with senior executives and the investment community
Excellent written communication skills with strong attention to detail and demonstrated ability to prepare market-facing materials
Highly organised with the ability to take initiative, work independently, and collaborate effectively within a team environment
Additional Information

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us. Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those with eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

DWS is seeking an experienced SAP SuccessFactors Senior Business Analyst to support a major HR Platform remediation and uplift program for our client.
This program will enhance and optimise SuccessFactors functionality across multiple modules and improve integration with key enterprise systems including ServiceNow, Payroll, and Dynamics 365.
The initiative focuses on simplifying the SuccessFactors landscape, uplifting processes across key modules, improving data integrity, and enabling a more streamlined hire‑to‑retire experience.

  
Type: Max Term OR ACN Contractor
Rate: up to $200K (inc super) OR up to $900/day
Start: Immediate
Location: Melbourne, VIC
Style: Hybrid, approx. 3 days per week in CBD office
  
  
All applicants must hold Australian Citizenship or Permanent Residency (PR) – DWS are unable to sponsor or support visas.

  
About the Role
As the SuccessFactors Business Analyst, you will play a critical role in defining, documenting, and validating requirements across various SuccessFactors modules. You will work closely with the Solution Architect, Lead BA, business SMEs, and technical delivery teams to uplift existing SuccessFactors configuration, optimise workflows, and support the broader HR technology ecosystem.
A deep understanding of SuccessFactors modules, upstream/downstream integrations, and HR process design is essential.


Key Responsibilities
SuccessFactors Requirements & Traceability

Elicit, document, and manage SuccessFactors-specific functional requirements, configuration needs, user stories, and acceptance criteria.
Ensure end‑to‑end traceability across EC, Talent, Recruitment, Learning, Performance, or other relevant modules (depending on scope).
Align requirements with SuccessFactors capability boundaries and integration touchpoints.
Process Mapping & Module Optimisation

Map as‑is and to‑be processes specifically within the SuccessFactors environment.
Identify process uplift opportunities within modules such as:
Employee Central, Recruitment (RCM/RMK), Onboarding, LMS, Performance & Goals, Compensation, Succession.
Functional Documentation

Produce SuccessFactors‑specific artefacts including:
Functional Requirement Documents (FRDs)
Configuration specifications
Integration requirements (SFTP, API, middleware)
Data dictionaries and data mapping documents
Stakeholder & Cross‑System Engagement

Act as a conduit between HR, Digital, Payroll, IT, and project teams.
Facilitate workshops focused on SuccessFactors capability, process pain points, and module optimisation.
Data Analysis & Migration

Analyse SuccessFactors data structures (e.g., EC Foundation Objects, MDF Objects, Position data).
Support migration and data cleansing activities, including data ingestion templates, validation rules, and field mapping.
Testing & Quality Assurance

Develop SuccessFactors-specific test cases and scenarios.
Support SIT/UAT to validate module configuration, workflows, business rules, and integrations.
  
  
About Us:
Since 1991, DWS has been helping organisations across Australia reimagine what’s possible through technology, business, and management consulting. With offices in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane, and Canberra, our 300+ locally based consultants bring deep expertise and fresh thinking to every project. We deliver end-to-end solutions spanning IT consulting, Staff Augmentation, Managed Delivery, Data & Analytics, Cloud, AI and Automation.
Our strength lies in our people; each consultant is carefully selected for their expertise, creativity, and commitment to excellence. Together, we deliver impactful solutions that drive innovation, efficiency, and long-term value. At DWS, we don’t just meet expectations - we redefine them.

Business Analyst - IS&T 
Zinc Australia, Regional Information Systems and Technology  
Townsville/ Mount Isa, Queensland, Australia 
Ref. No. 24536


The Operation
Mount Isa is a thriving city acting as a hub for regional business, transport, services, and government in North West Queensland.  Townsville located on the coast in tropical North Queensland, Glencore’s Townsville Operations encompass Copper Refineries Pty Ltd and Glencore Port Operations. Our Townsville Operations mark the final link in Glencore’s fully integrated north Queensland supply chain, connecting the natural resources we produce with markets around the world. 
We believe in the value of our people and our approach fosters the highest level of professionalism, ownership, and entrepreneurial spirit in all our people while never compromising on their safety and well-being.  

This role is eligible for relocation to either Townsville or Mount Isa.

The Role
We are looking for an experienced business analyst to join our Glencore Zinc Australia, Information Systems and Technology Department for a full-time ongoing position based in Mount Isa / Townsville.  Reporting to the Senior – Applications position, your main responsibilities will include supporting and aligning efforts to meet customer and business needs, eliciting and defining needs and recommending solutions that deliver value to stakeholders, managing stakeholder relationships and expectations, requirements management, and communication and participating in multiple projects by completing and updating project documentation.

Your key responsibilities include:

Engage with stakeholders to elicit, analyse, and validate business requirements through workshops, interviews, and documentation, ensuring alignment with IS&T strategic objectives
Translate business needs into clear, prioritised requirements and maintain effective communication between business units and technical colleagues throughout the project lifecycle
Conduct options analysis and vendor market research to identify fit-for-purpose solutions, evaluating alternatives based on functionality, cost, risk, and business alignment
Prepare detailed business cases to support decision-making, including cost-benefit analysis, risk assessment, and implementation recommendations
Produce high-quality artefacts such as requirements specifications, process maps, and functional documentation, and facilitate workshops to ensure stakeholder understanding and buy-in
Contribute to project planning activities, including scope definition, timelines, and resource requirements, and provide oversight during development and implementation to ensure requirements are realised
Act as a liaison between business stakeholders and technical colleagues, managing expectations and considering organisational impacts during solution delivery
Identify opportunities for process optimisation and system enhancements, ensuring solutions deliver measurable business value and support continuous improvement initiatives.

The successful applicants will have:

Bachelor's degree in Information Systems / Technology or related field
3+ years of experience as a Business Analyst (preferably IS&T related) or experience in a systems or data/analyst related role
Understands key technology building blocks and constraints (data models, interfaces, security, performance) and uses this knowledge to perform options analysis, evaluate vendor solutions, write fit-for-purpose requirements, and maintain end-to-end traceability from business need to delivered functionality
Strong communication skills, including prioritising, problem solving and interpersonal relationship building
A broad, enterprise-wide view of the business and appreciation for strategy, processes, and capabilities, enabling technologies, and governance
Experience modelling business processes using a variety of tools and techniques
Team player able to work effectively at all levels of an organization with the ability to influence others to move toward consensus
Relevant IS&T Certifications (e.g. Certified Business Analyst Professional CBAP and/or International Institute of Business Analysis (IIBA) accreditation) and your understanding or certification in BABOK (Business Analysis Book of Knowledge) is desirable.

Benefits:

Competitive remuneration package with 13% superannuation   and unrivalled career opportunities
Benefits program including discounts with Health Insurance providers, online and in-store discounts through Glencore Rewards, salary sacrificing vehicles, Employee Referral Program and Recognition and Reward Programs.

For any further questions please contact: Melody Grace on +61 475 704 838

Applications Close:  8.00am Monday 9th March 2026

About the role 

Join #TeamMB as our Data & Analytics Lead within the Digital & Technology Team in our Melbourne office. This newly created, full‑time permanent role is a key senior individual contributor position, where you will shape and lead enterprise-wide analytics initiatives. You’ll act as a strategic advisor to drive data‑informed decision-making across the organisation, while mentoring and uplifting capability within the analytics team to strengthen our data-driven culture.

In this role, you will:

Deliver executive‑level analytics, insights, and recommendations that shape strategic decision‑making.
Translate complex data into compelling, actionable presentations for senior leaders.
Lead the evolution of enterprise BI and influence data architecture direction across the firm.
Champion data quality, governance and a unified “single source of truth” culture.
Apply advanced analytical thinking to solve ambiguous problems and innovate in data‑sparse environments.
Partner with stakeholders to uplift data literacy and embed analytics into business decision‑making, bridging the gap between technical analysis and business language.
Build strong cross‑functional relationships and proactively identify opportunities where analytics can create business value — before you're asked.
Contribute to team capability, support key priorities, and maintain ongoing professional development.

The experience we are looking for 

5+ years’ experience in a hands‑on analytical or commercial role, with a track record of delivering meaningful insights that have influenced real business decisions.
Tertiary qualification in Economics, Business, Finance, Engineering, Statistics, or a related quantitative discipline.
Strong technical proficiency across SQL, Power BI, Qlik, and Excel – with the ability to own the full analytics life cycle from end-to-end, from raw data to executive recommendation.
Exceptional analytical and problem‑solving capability with a track record of generating meaningful, high‑impact insights.
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to simplify complex analytics and present clear, logical recommendations to senior leaders and non‑technical audiences – you’re as comfortable in a boardroom as you are in a database.
Proven ability to work effectively in, and lead, cross‑functional teams, driving collaboration and shared outcomes.
Demonstrates accountability, ownership, and a commitment to delivering high‑quality results.
Adept at resolving business challenges even when data is limited, applying creativity and resourcefulness.
Continuously strives for improvement and excellence, proactively identifying opportunities to enhance performance.

About Us

SBS is one of the world's most unique and innovative media organisations, producing trusted, meaningful, and engaging content that exists for all Australians to inspire, support and celebrate the diversity of our multicultural society.

The project involves the assessment and review of Home Health workforce, commercial assessment and workforce consideration to enable the development and implementation of a new suite of Home Health Enterprise Agreements (EAs). The project will assess current entitlements, financial impacts, and system implementation requirements to support the implementation of the new agreements.

Strong background in financial analysis and data modelling.
Experience with EA interpretation, especially in payroll or HR contexts.
Proficiency in Excel, Power BI, or similar analytical tools.
Understanding of award interpretation, penalty rates, and industrial relations frameworks.
Experience in system implementation or configuration (HRIS/Payroll and Time & Attendance systems).
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills.
Prior experience working on EA projects or industrial relations initiatives is ideal.
Familiarity with EAs in sectors like healthcare, aged care, hospitality, or government.
Ability to work independently and manage competing priorities.

Job Title: Solution Designer - SAS Experience / Credit Risk
Ad Text:
About the Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Solution Architect (SAS Experience) to lead the design and implementation of enterprise-scale data products within a complex Credit Risk and Banking environment.

This role will be responsible for delivering cross-functional data solutions across multiple platforms, ensuring enterprise reusability, strong governance, and alignment to architecture standards. You will work closely with business stakeholders, service owners, and technical teams to drive high-value data outcomes across risk and analytics programs.

Key Responsibilities

Design and implement cross-functional solutions that deliver enterprise data products across diverse technologies and platforms.

Engineer scalable and reusable data products across sourcing, design, data quality, transformation, and placement layers.

Define and oversee common enterprise components to improve delivery consistency and maintainability.

Architect solutions across multi-technology environments including SAS, Hadoop & Big Data ecosystems, Azure, Azure Machine Learning, Teradata, Informatica, and leading BI platforms.

Collaborate with Credit Risk stakeholders, Tech Leads, Service Owners, and Line of Business Leads to prioritise and size requirements and manage delivery backlogs.

Ensure alignment of projects and programs with enterprise design principles, standards, and governance frameworks.

Partner with business units to define and manage credit risk data elements, including reference data, metadata, and lineage.

Guide Agile delivery teams through design, development, testing, implementation, and support using modern full-stack and DevOps practices.

Skills & Experience

3+ years’ experience within a large, complex Credit Risk and/or Banking environment.

10+ years’ experience delivering business and technology solutions involving complex data engineering processes.

5+ years’ advanced SQL and SAS experience, including Base SAS, SAS Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Console, and overall SAS platform capability.

5+ years’ experience with Big Data and distributed technologies including Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase, Python, Java, Spring Boot, Git, Flink, CosmosDB, Akka, Scala, SQL, and Synapse.

Extensive experience in data warehousing, data modelling, and integration tools such as Informatica and Sterling.

Strong familiarity with BI tools including IBM Cognos/TM1, Power BI, and Tableau.

Proven experience designing cloud-based and serverless architectures, preferably within Microsoft Azure.

Experience delivering Risk Models and Analytics solutions using SAS RFW, SAS Risk Stratum, SAS Viya, and/or Azure Machine Learning.

Hands-on experience with DevOps pipelines, particularly Azure DevOps and Jenkins.

We're reimagining the way Australians live, work, and play. We own and manage some of the most recognisable and loved retail destinations across Australia.

We’re evolving our portfolio into destinations that offer a broad selection of retail, residential, and office spaces. Through our diverse portfolio, data-led decision-making, and nationwide development pipeline, we do things differently.

We’re looking for a Data Platform Manager who’s passionate about building scalable, secure, and high performing data platforms that power everything from analytics to machine learning and AI. In this role, you’ll lead the architecture, development, and operations of our enterprise data platforms—ensuring they are reliable, observable, trusted, and designed to support the organisation’s strategic ambitions. 

You’ll collaborate with engineers, architects, data scientists, analysts, and business stakeholders to create modern data environments that uplift decision making, embed data and AI governance, and accelerate innovation across Vicinity. 

What you’ll be doing 

Platform Architecture 

Design, develop, and maintain scalable data platform architectures aligned with business needs. 

Ensure data quality and seamless integration across multiple systems and sources. 

Own and enforce data security standards aligned to governance and privacy policies. 

Stay across emerging technologies to drive continuous platform innovation. 

Provide technical leadership and mentorship across the data and engineering teams. 

Translate complex data requirements into practical, high quality technical solutions. 

Platform Operations 

Lead day to day operations to ensure our data platforms are stable, secure, and high performing. 

Implement and govern MLOps practices to enable reliable model deployment, monitoring, and lifecycle management. 

Establish monitoring, observability, and alerting across all data pipelines and platforms. 

Coordinate the Data Engineering team to maintain platform reliability and operational excellence. 

Maintain high quality documentation, standards, and operational best practices. 

Partner closely with platform, security, and governance teams to uphold data privacy and compliance. 

Platform Engineering 

Design and manage ETL/ELT processes that ensure efficient, accurate data movement. 

Oversee development of data warehousing and lakehouse solutions that support ML, AI, and analytics. 

Optimise data workflows for performance, scalability, and resilience. 

Monitor, troubleshoot, and continuously improve ETL processes and data availability. 

Work with business and technical stakeholders to shape technical specifications from data requirements. 

What you’ll bring 

Essential Experience 

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or similar. 

10+ years in software development, including 7+ years across Data Analytics, Machine Learning, or AI. 

Expertise in data architecture across SQL and NoSQL ecosystems. 

Strong experience deploying containerised solutions. 

Proven capability delivering production grade data pipelines. 

Leadership experience managing Data Engineers and Platform Operations Engineers. 

Critical Knowledge 

Deep experience with at least one major cloud platform (AWS, GCP, or Azure). 

Proficiency in SQL and NoSQL technologies. 

Skilled in Python and JavaScript. 

Strong understanding of Docker and Kubernetes. 

CI/CD experience (e.g., BuildKite) and Gitbased code management. 

Databricks highly advantageous

Capabilities 

Advanced skills in CI/CD and modern DevOps for data and ML workloads. 

Ability to operationalise and deploy data pipelines, ML models, and AI services in containerised environments. 

Strong observability mindset—ensuring data reliability, model quality, and pipeline performance. 

Ability to build and mature data observability practices. 

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills. 

Strength in designing and delivering data platform solutions that enable ML and AI at scale. 

 Why join us? 

At Vicinity, you’ll be stepping into a role that sits at the intersection of data, digital innovation, and enterprise strategy. You’ll shape the foundations of our AI and analytics capabilities and influence how data drives our future. This is a rare opportunity to lead a modern data platform practice in an environment ready to invest, evolve, and innovate.

Strong time management and organisational skills with the ability to deliver to project timeframes.

Proven experience in journey mapping and translating insights into service/process improvements.
Strong capability in creating process maps, procedural and operational documents.
Experience working in the innovation industry or higher education (highly desirable).
Experience working on large, complex transformation programs in a consulting capacity.

About Brisbane City Council 

Brisbane City Council is Australia’s largest local government, responsible for shaping one of the fastest growing capital cities in the country. Council’s Brisbane Vision 2031 sets out the city’s long term aspirations: to be safe, inclusive, prosperous and globally connected, while retaining the lifestyle, character and subtropical vibrancy that make Brisbane unique. 

In the lead up to the 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games, Council is entering a defining era of transformation and reform. This is a once in a generation opportunity to deliver city shaping projects, integrated planning frameworks and sustainable economic development that will leave a lasting legacy. 

About the Role 

Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, the Manager, Financial Planning and Analysis is a senior executive leadership role within Strategic Finance, positioned at the centre of financial decision-making for one of Australia’s largest and most complex local governments. 

You will lead the transformation of Council’s FP&A capability through modern planning frameworks, rolling forecasts, advanced financial modelling, digital tools and data-driven insights, ensuring finance is future focused, agile and decision relevant. 

This is an opportunity to shape how finance partners with the business. You will act as a visible and trusted advisor to executive and operational leaders, with a clear mandate to challenge assumptions, elevate financial literacy and strengthen decision-making discipline across Council. 

The role offers significant visibility across the organisation and the opportunity to influence outcomes that directly impact the future of Brisbane. As a member of Council’s executive leadership cohort, you will contribute beyond the FP&A function, participating in organisational strategy, governance and reform initiatives and supporting enterprise-wide performance excellence. 

Key aspects of the role include: 

Leading the development of Council’s annual budget, long-term financial plan and forecasting framework, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities and service delivery outcomes 
Providing high-quality financial modelling, scenario analysis and insights to support executive decision-making and major initiatives 
Establishing and embedding a strong finance business partnering approach across diverse service areas 
Driving continuous improvement in financial planning processes, systems and analytics capability 
Translating complex financial information into clear, practical insights that support confident and timely decisions 
Leading and developing a high-performing team while contributing to broader organisational strategy and transformation initiatives 
This role will suit a finance leader who enjoys operating in a complex environment, influencing beyond traditional finance boundaries and building capability across an organisation. It offers the opportunity to combine strategic thinking with tangible impact, supporting long-term financial sustainability and delivering value for the Brisbane community. 

As an Executive Service leader, you will contribute beyond the FP&A function, participating in whole-of-Council strategy, governance, reform and performance initiatives. This includes engaging with senior executives and elected members, and providing trusted, independent financial advice in complex, high-accountability environments. 

About You 

You are an experienced enterprise FP&A leader with strong financial planning and analysis capability and a demonstrated ability to influence decision-making in complex organisations. You bring a strategic mindset, balanced with strong operational understanding, and are comfortable working closely with senior executives to drive outcomes. 

You will demonstrate: 

Extensive experience in financial planning and analysis, budgeting and forecasting within a large or complex organisation 
Advanced financial modelling and scenario planning capability 
A strong track record of business partnering with executive and operational leaders 
The ability to translate complex financial data into clear commercial insights and recommendations 
Experience improving financial systems, processes or planning frameworks 
Strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills across diverse groups 
A collaborative and people focused leadership style with experience building high performing teams 
A strong understanding of public sector governance, accountability frameworks and the unique challenges of local government finance 
Experience operating in, or closely with, highly regulated or public accountability environments, with a strong understanding of governance, stewardship and legislative context. 
To be eligible for this position, tertiary qualifications in accounting, business or a related discipline are required. You must hold CPA or CA accreditation (or equivalent Australian recognition). Postgraduate qualifications in management or public administration will be highly regarded.
